					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Confusion is likely due to my terseness (but at least anyone can correct that).
<br />
<br />Reading from $2007 when the VRAM address is $3fxx will fill the internal read buffer with the contents at VRAM address $3fxx, in addition to reading the palette RAM.
<br />
<br />The "third byte masking" refers to the third byte (attributes) of each sprite not having all bits implemented, where writing $ff is equivalent to writing $e3.</div>

